/-!
# The [[4, 2, 2]] four-qubit code (also known as `C₄` or "Little Shor code")

A four-qubit hyperbolic self-dual CSS detection code with **two logical qubits**
and distance 2. Originally introduced in
[Vaidman–Goldenberg–Wiesner 1996, `arxiv:quant-ph/9603031`] and
[Grassl–Beth–Pellizzari 1996, `arxiv:quant-ph/9610042`].

The stabilizer is generated by two operators: `XXXX` and `ZZZZ`. The four
codeword basis states are
```
|0̄0̄⟩ = (|0000⟩ + |1111⟩)/√2
|0̄1̄⟩ = (|0011⟩ + |1100⟩)/√2
|1̄0̄⟩ = (|0101⟩ + |1010⟩)/√2
|1̄1̄⟩ = (|0110⟩ + |1001⟩)/√2
```
giving logical operators
```
X̄₁ = IXIX,  X̄₂ = IIXX,  Z̄₁ = IIZZ,  Z̄₂ = IZIZ.
```

This file is a **Stage-2 skeleton**: every theorem ends in a `sorry` tagged
`TODO(stab_4_2_2-T<n>): …`. Stage 4 closes them following the Steane7
template, scaled down to 4 qubits and adapted for k = 2.
-/

open NQubitPauliGroupElement

/-! ## Generators -/

/-- Z-check stabilizer: `ZZZZ` (Z on every qubit). -/
def Z1 : NQubitPauliGroupElement 4 :=
  ⟨0,
    (((NQubitPauliOperator.identity 4).set 0 PauliOperator.Z).set 1 PauliOperator.Z).set 2
      PauliOperator.Z |>.set 3 PauliOperator.Z⟩

/-- X-check stabilizer: `XXXX` (X on every qubit). -/
def X1 : NQubitPauliGroupElement 4 :=
  ⟨0,
    (((NQubitPauliOperator.identity 4).set 0 PauliOperator.X).set 1 PauliOperator.X).set 2
      PauliOperator.X |>.set 3 PauliOperator.X⟩

/-- The single Z-check generator. -/
def ZGenerators : Set (NQubitPauliGroupElement 4) :=
  {Z1}

/-- The single X-check generator. -/
def XGenerators : Set (NQubitPauliGroupElement 4) :=
  {X1}

/-- The full generator set: one Z-check and one X-check. -/
def generators : Set (NQubitPauliGroupElement 4) :=
  ZGenerators ∪ XGenerators

/-- The [[4, 2, 2]] stabilizer subgroup: closure of `{ZZZZ, XXXX}`. -/
noncomputable def subgroup : Subgroup (NQubitPauliGroupElement 4) :=
  Subgroup.closure generators

